### Directory Structure

```text
RealRain-2k/
└── images/
    ├── RR2K-C0001_R010_E01_K3000_F0502_P01.jpg
    ├── ...
    └── RR2K-X0080_R290_X3000M_K5000_F0140_P02.jpg
```

### Filename Convention

Core samples use:

```text
RR2K-Cxxxx_Rxxx_Exx_Kxxxx_Fxxxx_Pxx.jpg
```

- `Cxxxx`: core-sample ID
- `Rxxx`: nominal rainfall intensity in mm/h, from `R010` to `R400`
- `Exx`: exposure-setting code, from `E01` (1/1000 s) to `E12` (1/10 s)
- `Kxxxx`: nominal color temperature: `K3000`, `K4000`, `K5000`, or `K6000`
- `Fxxxx`: source-frame ID
- `Pxx`: spatial patch ID derived from that source frame

Extreme samples use the prefix `RR2K-X`. An exposure token such as `X3000M` represents an exposure time of 3000 ms.

> **Note:** Multiple patches may originate from the same source frame. When creating training and test splits, all images sharing the same `Fxxxx` source-frame ID should remain in the same subset to prevent data leakage.

If you use this dataset, please cite the corresponding MarineRain paper.
